        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 27 at 3:08PM MDT by NWS Denver CO</headline>
        <description>At 308 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 5
miles north of Ponderosa Park, or 24 miles southeast of Denver,
moving northeast at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Ponderosa Park.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
